      "Prosciutto is the generic term for an Italian dry -cured ham. Characterized by a sweet, delicate flavor, it is often served thinly sliced and raw in a style known as prosciutto crudo. The curing process makes the raw ham safe to eat. When it is served cooked, it is called prosciutto cotto. The most famous prosciutto variety is Prosciutto di Parma PDO, which comes from the Emilia -Romagna region in Italy's north. The PDO designation stands for Protected Designation of Origin and signifies t hat the product is authentic and meets certain standards of quality.",
