      "Diving is the sport of plunging into water from a platform or springboard, usually while d performing acrobatics. Although diving contests were held in England in the 1800s, it was not until 1903 that it formally became a competitive sport. I t was added to the Sum mer Olympic Games a year later. The sport originated in Europe in the early 1800s. It allowed gymnasts to perform elaborate acrobatic feats without fear of injury from impact with the ground. Even today, gymnasts are particularly “disposed” to becoming professional divers, and many do. Both sports have similar requirements for strength, flexibility, and the ability to judge one's position while moving through the air.",
